Differential diagnosis . The new species is most similar to
Diversipes sineunguibus Khaustov, 2015
, described from Chile ( Khaustov 2015 ) by the absence of claws on tarsus IV, absence of setae v” on femora I and II and similar lengths of dorsal idiosomal setae. It can be distinguished from the latter by the presence of setae ps 2 (vs. absent in
D. sineunguibus
), by absence of setae v’ on genu I and s on tibiotarsus I (vs. present in
D. sineunguibus
), by vestigial eupathidia ( ft ) (vs. well developed in
D. sineunguibus
), and by distinctly thickened setae ps 1 and ps 3 (vs. slightly thickened in
D. sineunguibus
).
